Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Trim @carrot{3%ounce}; using a #peeler{}, shave carrot lengthwise into ribbons, rotating as you go, until you get to the core. Discard core. Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into ¼-inch-thick half-moons. Trim and remove strings from @sugar snap peas{4%ounce}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add ginger and cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water (2¼ cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine scallion whites, @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, and a pinch of salt; set aside to pickle.

In a separate small bowl, combine @sesame oil{1%tablespoon}, @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, @sriracha{1%teaspoon}, and @sugar{1%tablespoon}.

Rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water; pat shrimp dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{}, preferably nonstick, over medium-high heat. Add shrimp; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan, preferably nonstick, over medium-high heat. Add carrot and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until just tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Transfer to a #medium bowl{}.

Add zucchini and another drizzle of oil to pan. Cook, stirring, until tender, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer to bowl with carrot.

Use pan used for shrimp here.

Add snap peas and another drizzle of oil to same pan. Cook, undisturbed, until charred on one side, ~{1-2%minutes}. Continue to cook, stirring occasionally, until tender and charred all over, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Season with salt and pepper.

Turn off heat; transfer to bowl with veggies.

Optional: Wipe out pan. Heat a drizzle of oil in pan over medium heat. Once hot, crack @eggs{2}(fried) into pan and cover. (For 4 servings, use four eggs; you may want to cook eggs in batches.) Fry eggs to preference. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{}. Arrange carrot, zucchini, and snap peas on top. Top each bowl with fried eggs (if using) and pickled scallion whites (draining first). Drizzle with sauce and any remaining Sriracha to taste. Sprinkle with scallion greens and serve.

Top rice with shrimp along with veggies.

> Wash hands and surfaces after handling raw eggs. Consuming raw or undercooked eggs may increase your risk of foodborne illness.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.